Question 1: Explain the structure of an HTML table and the purpose of each element (<table>, <tr>, <th>, <td>, <thead>).
ANS=

Structure of an HTML Table:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <table align="center" border="1px" cellpading="5" cellspacing="0" height="500px" width="700px" >
        <thead>
        <tr>
            <td>Product Name</td>
            <td>image</td>
            <td>price</td>
            <td>Description</td>
            <td>Availanity</td>
            
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tr>
            <td>Wireless Headphone</td>
            <td><img src="headphones.png" alt="" height="50px"></td>
            <td>2,499</td>
            <td>Bluetooth 5.2,ANC,30h Battery</td>
            <td>In Stock</td>
            
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Smartphone (A)</td>
            <td rowspan="2"><img src="smartphone.png" alt="" height="50px"></td>
            <td rowspan="2">4,999</td>
            <td rowspan="2">6.5 AMOLED,256GB,12GB RAM</td>
            <td>In Stock</td>
            
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Smartphone (B)</td>
            
            
            <td>low Srock</td>
            
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Laptop</td>
            <td><img src="laptop.png" alt="" height="50px"></td>
            <td>10,000</td>
            <td>13th Genaration intel,Window 11,8GB LPDDR5,512GB SSD</td>
            <td>In Stock</td>
            
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Smart Watch</td>
            <td><img src="smartwatch.png" alt="" height="50px"></td>
            <td>3,999</td>
            <td>Water resistence,sensors</td>
            <td>Out of Stock</td>
            
        </tr>
    </table>
    
</body>
</html>

-->> Purpose of elements:

1.<table> → Defines the table structure.
2.<tr> (table row) → Defines a single row inside the table.
3.<th> (table header cell) → Defines a header cell (bold + centered by default). Used for column/row headings.
4.<td> (table data cell) → Defines a normal data cell inside the table.
5.<thead> (table head) → Groups header rows (<tr> + <th>). Helpful for accessibility, SEO, and styling.

